title: The Trews - House of Ill Fame (2003)
description:
In 2002, the Trews won southern Ontario&#039;s 97.7 HTZ-FM&#039;s annual Rock Search contest. This brought them attention from Big Sugar singer Gordon Johnson, who produced the group&#039;s self-titled EP and brought them along on tour with his band. In 2003, with Sony Music Canada, the Trews released their first full-length album, House of Ill Fame.
